quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  7,121,"They said, "We believe in the Lord of the worlds,"
  7,122,"the Lord of Musa and Harun.""
  7,123,"The Pharaoh said, 'You have believed in him before I permitted you. No doubt, this is a device you have devised in the city, so that you may expel it's people from there. Now you shall know (it's end)."
  7,124,"I shall certainly, cut apart your hands and your legs from opposite sides. Then I shall crucify you all together.""
  7,125,"They said, "We are surely to return to our Lord."
  7,126,"you punish us for no other reason but that we have believed in the signs of our Lord when they came to us. "0 our Lord, pour out patience upon us and let the death take us while we are Muslims ( the faithful).""
  7,127,"And the chiefs of the people of the Pharaoh said, "Do you leave Musa (علیہ السلام) and his people that they spread disorder in the land while he leaves you and your gods?" He said, " We shall slaughter their sons and let their women live. And we have full power over them.""
  7,128,"And Musa said to his people," "Seek help from Allah and be patient. Surely, the land belongs to Allah. He lets whomsoever He wills, from among His slaves, inherit it. And the end-result is in favour of the God-fearing.""
  7,129,"They said, "We were persecuted before you came to us, as well as, after you have come to us." He said, "It is likely that your Lord will destroy your enemy and make you successors in the earth, then He will see how you act.""
  7,130,"And We seized the people of the Pharaoh with years of famine and loss of fruits, so that they may take lesson."